    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Available for the discerning collector is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in exemplary condition. This specimen features the high-revving S54B32 3.2L inline-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies and a 11.5:1 compression ratio to achieve a linear power band up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Mechanically, the vehicle has been future-proofed: the double-VANOS system has been fully overhauled, and the rod bearings have been replaced with treated shells. The chassis is structurally perfect, featuring a proactive subframe reinforcement to maintain the integrity of the rear mounting points. Power is managed via a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission and a Variable M Differential Lock, ensuring optimal torque distribution. The suspension retains its factory-spec damping and bushings, offering the precise turn-in and telepathic feedback characteristic of a true driver's machine. Zero deferred maintenance and a flawless service history.",
      "price": 46500.0,
